Privacy Policy
Effective Date:
April 29 2024
kokotoots understands the importance of privacy, especially for children. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose information from and about users of our mobile application (“App”).
What Information Do We Collect?
We do not collect any personal information from users of our App. This means we do not collect things like names, email addresses, or device identifiers. We also do not track or store any information about your child’s activity within the App.
How Do We Use the Information We Collect?
Since we do not collect any personal information, we do not use any information for any purpose.
Sharing Your Information
We do not share any information with any third parties. This includes other companies, organizations, and individuals.
Security
kokotoots takes reasonable measures to protect against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction of any information we receive. However, no internet transmission or electronic storage is ever completely secure.
Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post any changes on this page.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
[Insert Your Email Address]
Compliance with COPPA
Our App is designed for children under the age of 13. We comply with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (“COPPA”). We do not collect any personal information from children without verifiable parental consent.
Additional Information for Parents
As a parent, you can help protect your child’s privacy by:
Reviewing this Privacy Policy with your child.
Talking to your child about safe and responsible online practices.